msgid "3D rendering limitations"
msgstr "Teorainneacha rindreála 3D"

msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Réamhrá"

msgid ""
"Due to their focus on performance, real-time rendering engines have many "
"limitations. Godot's renderer is no exception. To work effectively with "
"those limitations, you need to understand them."
msgstr ""
"Mar gheall ar a bhfócas ar fheidhmíocht, tá go leor teorainneacha ag innill "
"reddála fíor-ama. Ní haon eisceacht é renderóir Godot. Chun oibriú go "
"héifeachtach leis na teorainneacha sin, ní mór duit iad a thuiscint."

msgid "Texture size limits"
msgstr "teorainneacha méide uigeachta"

msgid ""
"On desktops and laptops, textures larger than 8192×8192 may not be supported "
"on older devices. You can check your target GPU's limitations on `GPUinfo."
"org <https://www.gpuinfo.org/>`__."
msgstr ""
"Ar ríomhairí deisce agus ríomhairí glúine, d’fhéadfadh sé nach dtacaítear le "
"huigeachtaí níos mó ná 8192×8192 ar ghléasanna níos sine. Is féidir leat "
"teorainneacha do sprioc-GPU a sheiceáil ar `GPUinfo.org <https://www.gpuinfo."
"org/>`__."

msgid ""
"Mobile GPUs are typically limited to 4096×4096 textures. Also, some mobile "
"GPUs don't support repeating non-power-of-two-sized textures. Therefore, if "
"you want your texture to display correctly on all platforms, you should "
"avoid using textures larger than 4096×4096 and use a power of two size if "
"the texture needs to repeat."
msgstr ""
"De ghnáth bíonn GPUanna soghluaiste teoranta do 4096 × 4096 uigeachtaí. "
"Chomh maith leis sin, ní thacaíonn roinnt GPUanna soghluaiste le uigeachtaí "
"neamh-chumhachta dhá mhéide athrá Dá bhrí sin, más mian leat d'uigeacht a "
"thaispeáint i gceart ar gach ardán, ba cheart duit uigeachtaí níos mó ná "
"4096 × 4096 a sheachaint a úsáid agus cumhacht dhá mhéid a úsáid más gá an "
"uigeacht a athdhéanamh."

msgid ""
"To limit the size of a specific texture that may be too large to render, you "
"can set the **Process > Size Limit** import option to a value greater than "
"``0``. This will reduce the texture's dimensions on import (preserving "
"aspect ratio) without affecting the source file."
msgstr ""
"Chun méid uigeachta ar leith a d'fhéadfadh a bheith rómhór le rindreáil a "
"theorannú, is féidir leat an rogha iompórtála **Próiseas > Teorainn Méid** a "
"shocrú go luach níos mó ná ``0``. Laghdóidh sé seo toisí an uigeachta ar "
"allmhairiú (cóimheas gné a chaomhnú) gan cur isteach ar an gcomhad foinse."

msgid "Color banding"
msgstr "Bandáil dathanna"

msgid ""
"When using the Forward+ or Forward Mobile rendering methods, Godot's 3D "
"engine renders internally in HDR. However, the rendering output will be "
"tonemapped to a low dynamic range so it can be displayed on the screen. This "
"can result in visible banding, especially when using untextured materials. "
"For performance reasons, color precision is also lower when using the "
"Forward Mobile rendering method compared to Forward+."
msgstr ""
"Agus na modhanna rindreála Forward+nó Forward Mobile á úsáid agat, déanann "
"inneall 3D Godot a léiriú go hinmheánach i HDR. Mar sin féin, déanfar an t-"
"aschur rindreála tonemapú go raon dinimiciúil íseal ionas gur féidir é a "
"thaispeáint ar an scáileán. D'fhéadfadh bandáil infheicthe a bheith mar "
"thoradh air seo, go háirithe agus ábhair neamh-uigeachta á úsáid agat Ar "
"chúiseanna feidhmíochta, tá cruinneas datha níos ísle freisin agus an modh "
"rindreála Forward Mobile á úsáid agat i gcomparáid le Forward +."

msgid ""
"When using the Compatibility rendering method, HDR is not used and the color "
"precision is the lowest of all rendering methods. This also applies to 2D "
"rendering, where banding may be visible when using smooth gradient textures."
msgstr ""
"Agus an modh rindreála Comhoiriúnachta á úsáid, ní úsáidtear HDR agus is é "
"an cruinneas dath an ceann is ísle de na modhanna rindreála go léir. "
"Baineann sé seo freisin le rindreáil 2T, áit a bhféadfadh bandáil a bheith "
"le feiceáil agus uigeachtaí míne grádáin á n-úsáid."

msgid "There are two main ways to alleviate banding:"
msgstr "Tá dhá phríomhbhealach ann chun bandáil a mhaolú:"

msgid ""
"Alternatively, bake some noise into your textures. This is mainly effective "
"in 2D, e.g. for vignetting effects. In 3D, you can also use a `custom "
"debanding shader <https://github.com/fractilegames/godot-gles2-debanding-"
"material>`__ to be applied on your *materials*. This technique works even if "
"your project is rendered with low color precision, which means it will work "
"when using the Mobile and Compatibility rendering methods."
msgstr ""
"De rogha air sin, cuir roinnt torainn isteach i d’uigeachtaí. Tá sé seo "
"éifeachtach go príomha i 2D, e.g. le haghaidh éifeachtaí vignetting. I 3D, "
"is féidir leat `scáilitheoir díbhannaí saincheaptha <https://github.com/"
"fractilegames/godot-gles2-debanding-material>`__ a úsáid freisin le cur i "
"bhfeidhm ar do *ábhair*. Oibríonn an teicníocht seo fiú má tá do thionscadal "
"rindreáilte le cruinneas íseal dath, rud a chiallaíonn go n-oibreoidh sé "
"agus na modhanna rindreála Soghluaiste agus Comhoiriúnachta á n-úsáid agat."

msgid "Color banding comparison (contrast increased for more visibility)"
msgstr ""
"Comparáid bandála dathanna (méadaíodh codarsnacht le haghaidh níos infhe"

msgid ""
"See `Banding in Games: A Noisy Rant (PDF) <https://loopit.dk/"
"banding_in_games.pdf>`__ for more details about banding and ways to combat "
"it."
msgstr ""
"Féach `Banding in Games: A Noisy Rant (PDF) <https://loopit.dk/"
"banding_in_games.pdf>`__ le haghaidh tuilleadh sonraí maidir le bandáil agus "
"bealaí chun é a chomhrac."

msgid "Depth buffer precision"
msgstr "Cruinneas maolán doimhne"

msgid ""
"To sort objects in 3D space, rendering engines rely on a *depth buffer* "
"(also called *Z-buffer*). This buffer has a finite precision: 24-bit on "
"desktop platforms, sometimes 16-bit on mobile platforms (for performance "
"reasons). If two different objects end up on the same buffer value, then Z-"
"fighting will occur. This will materialize as textures flickering back and "
"forth as the camera moves or rotates."
msgstr ""
"Chun rudaí a shórtáil i spás 3D, bíonn innill rindreála ag brath ar *maolán "
"doimhneachta* (ar a dtugtar *Z-maolán* freisin). Tá cruinneas teoranta ag an "
"maolán seo: 24-giotán ar ardáin deisce, uaireanta 16-giotán ar ardáin "
"soghluaiste (ar chúiseanna feidhmíochta). Má chríochnaíonn dhá rud dhifriúla "
"ar an luach maolánach céanna, ansin tarlóidh Z-troid. Rachaidh sé seo i "
"gcrích agus uigeachtaí ag caochadh anonn is anall de réir mar a ghluaiseann "
"nó a rothlaíonn an ceamara."

msgid ""
"To make the depth buffer more precise over the rendered area, you should "
"*increase* the Camera node's **Near** property. However, be careful: if you "
"set it too high, players will be able to see through nearby geometry. You "
"should also *decrease* the Camera node's **Far** property to the lowest "
"permissible value for your use case, though keep in mind it won't impact "
"precision as much as the **Near** property."
msgstr ""
"Chun an maolán doimhneachta a dhéanamh níos cruinne thar an limistéar "
"rindreáilte, ba cheart duit* maoin **Gear** an nód Ceamara a mhéadú*. Mar "
"sin féin, bí cúramach: má shocraíonn tú é ró-ard, beidh imreoirí in ann a "
"fheiceáil trí ghéimseadracht in aice láimhe. Ba chóir duit* maoin **Far** an "
"nód Ceamara a laghdú* go dtí an luach is ísle incheadaithe le do chás "
"úsáide, ach coinnigh i gcuimhne ní bheidh tionchar aige ar chruinneas an "
"oiread agus an maoin **Near-**."

msgid ""
"If you only need high precision when the player can see far away, you could "
"change it dynamically based on the game conditions. For instance, if the "
"player enters an airplane, the **Near** property can be temporarily "
"increased to avoid Z-fighting in the distance. It can then be decreased once "
"the player leaves the airplane."
msgstr ""
"Mura dteastaíonn cruinneas ard uait ach nuair is féidir leis an imreoir a "
"fheiceáil i bhfad ar shiúl, d'fhéadfá é a athrú go dinimiciúil bunaithe ar "
"choinníoll Mar shampla, má théann an t-imreoir isteach in eitleán, is féidir "
"an maoin **Near** a mhéadú go sealadach chun troid Z a sheachaint san achar. "
"Is féidir é a laghdú ansin nuair a fhágann an t-imreoir an t-eitleán."

msgid ""
"Depending on the scene and viewing conditions, you may also be able to move "
"the Z-fighting objects further apart without the difference being visible to "
"the player."
msgstr ""
"Ag brath ar an radharc agus ar na coinníollacha féachana, b'fhéidir go "
"mbeidh tú in ann na rudaí troid Z a bhogadh níos faide óna chéile gan an "
"difríocht a bheith le feiceáil don imreoir."

msgid ""
"Z-fighting comparison (before and after tweaking the scene by offsetting the "
"Label3D away from the floor)"
msgstr ""
"Comparáid comhrac Z (roimh agus tar éis an radharc a athrú tríd an Label3D a "
"fhritháireamh ar shiúl ón urlár)"

msgid "Transparency sorting"
msgstr "Sórtáil trédhearc"

msgid ""
"In Godot, transparent materials are drawn after opaque materials. "
"Transparent objects are sorted back to front before being drawn based on the "
"Node3D's position, not the vertex position in world space. Due to this, "
"overlapping objects may often be sorted out of order. To fix improperly "
"sorted objects, tweak the material's :ref:`Render Priority "
"<class_Material_property_render_priority>` property or the node's :ref:"
"`Sorting Offset <class_VisualInstance3D_property_sorting_offset>`. Render "
"Priority will force specific materials to appear in front of or behind other "
"transparent materials, while Sorting Offset will move the object forward or "
"backward for the purpose of sorting. Even then, these may not always be "
"sufficient."
msgstr ""
"I Godot, tarraingítear ábhair thrédhearcacha tar éis ábhair teimhneach. "
"Déantar réada trédhearcacha a shórtáil siar chun tosaigh sula dtarraingítear "
"iad bunaithe ar shuíomh an Node3D, ní ar shuíomh na rinn sa spás domhanda. "
"Mar gheall air seo, is minic go mbíonn rudaí forluiteacha curtha in ord in "
"ord. Chun réada atá sórtáilte go míchuí a shocrú, tweak :tag:`Tosaíocht "
"Rindreála <class_Material_property_render_priority>` airí nó :ref:"
"`Fritháireamh Sórtáil <class_VisualInstance3D_property_sorting_offset>` an "
"ábhair. Cuirfidh Tosaíocht Rindreála iallach ar ábhair shonracha láithriú os "
"comhair nó taobh thiar d’ábhair thrédhearcacha eile, agus bogfaidh Sórtáil "
"Fritháireamh an réad ar aghaidh nó siar chun críche sórtála. Fiú amháin "
"ansin, b’fhéidir nach leor iad seo i gcónaí."

msgid ""
"Some rendering engines feature *order-independent transparency* techniques "
"to alleviate this, but this is costly on the GPU. Godot currently doesn't "
"provide this feature. There are still several ways to avoid this problem:"
msgstr ""
"Tá teicnícke*trédhearcacht neamhspleách ar ordú* ag roinnt innill rindreála "
"chun é seo a mhaolú, ach tá sé seo costasach ar an GPU. Faoi láthair ní "
"sholáthraíonn Godot an ghné seo. Tá bealaí éagsúla ann fós chun an fhadhb "
"seo a sheachaint:"

msgid ""
"Only make materials transparent if you actually need it. If a material only "
"has a small transparent part, consider splitting it into a separate "
"material. This will allow the opaque part to cast shadows and will also "
"improve performance."
msgstr ""
"Ní déan ábhair trédhearcach ach má theastaíonn uait i ndáiríre. Mura bhfuil "
"ach cuid bheag trédhearcach ag ábhar, smaoinigh ar é a roinnt ina ábhar ar "
"leithligh. Ligfidh sé seo don chuid trédhearcach scáthanna a chaitheamh agus "
"feabhsóidh sé feidhmíocht freisin."

msgid ""
"If your texture mostly has fully opaque and fully transparent areas, you can "
"use alpha testing instead of alpha blending. This transparency mode is "
"faster to render and doesn't suffer from transparency issues. Enable "
"**Transparency > Transparency** to **Alpha Scissor** in StandardMaterial3D, "
"and adjust **Transparency > Alpha Scissor Threshold** accordingly if needed. "
"Note that MSAA will not antialias the texture's edges unless alpha "
"antialiasing is enabled in the material's properties. However, FXAA, TAA and "
"supersampling will be able to antialias the texture's edges regardless of "
"whether alpha antialiasing is enabled on the material."
msgstr ""
"Má tá limistéir atá go hiomlán teimhneach agus go hiomlán trédhearcach den "
"chuid is mó ag d'uigeacht, is féidir leat tástáil alfa a úsáid in ionad "
"cumasc alfa. Is féidir an modh trédhearcachta seo a sholáthar níos tapúla "
"agus ní bhíonn fadhbanna trédhearcachta ann. Cumasaigh **Trédhearcacht > "
"Trédhearcacht** go **Alpha Scissor** i StandardMaterial3D, agus coigeartaigh "
"**Trédhearcacht > Tairseach Siosúr Alfa** dá réir más gá. Tabhair faoi deara "
"nach ndéanfaidh MSAA imill na huigeachta frithaliasú mura rud é go bhfuil "
"alfa-frithaliasú cumasaithe in airíonna an ábhair. Mar sin féin, beidh FXAA, "
"TAA agus supersampling in ann antialias imill an uigeachta is cuma an bhfuil "
"antialiasing alfa cumasaithe ar an ábhar."

msgid ""
"If you need to render semi-transparent areas of the texture, alpha scissor "
"isn't suitable. Instead, setting the StandardMaterial3D's **Transparency > "
"Transparency** property to **Depth Pre-Pass** can sometimes work (at a "
"performance cost). You can also try the **Alpha Hash** mode."
msgstr ""
"Más gá duit achair leath-trédhearcacha den uigeacht a sholáthar, níl an "
"siosúr alfa oiriúnach. Ina áit sin, uaireanta is féidir oibriú uaireanta (ar "
"chostas feidhmíochta) chun maoin **Trédhearcacht > Trédhearcacht** an "
"StandardMaterial3D a shocrú go **Doimhneacht Réamhphas**. Is féidir leat "
"freisin triail a bhaint as an modh **Alfa Hash**."

msgid ""
"If you want a material to fade with distance, use the StandardMaterial3D "
"distance fade mode **Pixel Dither** or **Object Dither** instead of **Pixel "
"Alpha**. This will make the material opaque, which also speeds up rendering."
msgstr ""
"Más mian leat go n-éireoidh ábhar le fad, bain úsáid as an modh éadú achair "
"caighdeánMaterial3D**Pixel Dither** nó **Object Dither** in ionad**Pixel "
"Alfa**. Déanfaidh sé seo an t-ábhar trédhearcach, a chuireann luasú le "
"rindreáil freisin."

msgid ""
"Transparency sorting comparison (alpha-blended materials on the left, alpha "
"scissor materials on the right)"
msgstr ""
"Comparáid sórtála trédhearcachta (ábhair chumasctha alfa ar chlé, ábhair "
"siosúr alfa ar dheis)"

msgid "Multi-sample antialiasing"
msgstr "Antialiasing ilshamplach"

msgid ""
"Antialiasing is explained in detail on the :ref:`doc_3d_antialiasing` page."
msgstr ""
"Mínítear antialiasing go mion ar an leathanach:ref: `doc_3d_antialiasing`."

msgid ""
"Multi-sample antialiasing (MSAA) takes multiple *coverage* samples at the "
"edges of polygons when rendering objects. It does not increase the number of "
"*color* samples used to render a scene. Here's what this means in practice:"
msgstr ""
"Tógann antialiasing il-shamplaí (MSAA) samplaí* clúdaithe* iolracha ag imill "
"na bpolagóin agus rudaí á rindreáil. Ní mhéadaíonn sé líon na samplaí* dath* "
"a úsáidtear chun radharc a léiriú. Seo a chiallaíonn sé seo go praiticiúil:"

msgid ""
"Edges of meshes will be smoothed out nicely (as well as supersampling would)."
msgstr ""
"Déanfar imill na mogalra a réiteach go deas (chomh maith le supersampláil)."

msgid ""
"Transparent materials that use *alpha testing* (1-bit transparency) won't be "
"smoothed out."
msgstr ""
"Ní dhéanfar ábhair thrédhearcacha a úsáideann tástáil alfa* (trédhearcacht 1-"
"giotán) a réiteach."

msgid ""
"Specular aliasing (\"sparkles\" that appear on reflective surfaces) won't be "
"reduced."
msgstr ""
"Ní laghdófar aileasú speisialta (“spréilí” atá le feiceáil ar dhromchlaí "
"frithchaiteacha)."

msgid ""
"There are several ways to work around this limitation depending on your "
"performance budget:"
msgstr ""
"Tá roinnt bealaí ann chun oibriú timpeall ar an teorainn seo ag brath ar do "
"bhuiséad feidhmíochta:"

msgid ""
"To make specular aliasing less noticeable, open the Project Settings and "
"enable **Rendering > Quality > Screen Space Filters > Screen Space Roughness "
"Limiter**. This filter has a moderate cost on performance, so it should only "
"be enabled if you actually need it."
msgstr ""
"Chun an t-ailiasacht amhantrach a dhéanamh níos lú faoi deara, oscail "
"Socruithe an Tionscadail agus cumasaigh ** Rindreáil > Cáilíocht > Scagairí "
"Spáis Scáileáin > Teorantóir Garmhachta Spás Scáileáin**. Tá costas "
"measartha ar fheidhmíocht ag an scagaire seo, mar sin níor cheart é a "
"chumasú ach amháin má tá sé de dhíth ort i ndáiríre."

msgid ""
"Enable fast approximate antialiasing (FXAA) in addition to (or instead of) "
"MSAA. Since FXAA is a screen-space antialiasing method, it will smooth out "
"anything. As a downside, FXAA also makes the scene appear blurrier, "
"especially at resolutions below 1440p. FXAA also lacks temporal information, "
"which means its impact on specular aliasing is limited."
msgstr ""
"Cumasaigh frith-thart tapa (FXAA) i dteannta (nó in ionad) MSAA. Ós rud é "
"gur modh antialiasing spáis scáileáin é FXAA, déanfaidh sé rud ar bith a "
"réiteach. Mar mhíbhuntáiste, déanann FXAA an radharc níos doiléire freisin, "
"go háirithe ag rúin faoi bhun 1440p. Níl faisnéis ama ag FXAA freisin, rud a "
"chiallaíonn go bhfuil a thionchar ar aliasing speisialta teoranta."

msgid ""
"Enable temporal antialiasing (TAA) in addition to (or instead of) MSAA. "
"Since TAA is a screen-space antialiasing method, it will smooth out "
"anything. As a downside, TAA also makes the scene appear blurrier, "
"especially at resolutions below 1440p. TAA provides superior quality "
"compared to FXAA and can effectively combat specular aliasing. However, TAA "
"has a greater performance cost compared to FXAA, and TAA can introduce "
"ghosting artifacts with fast movement."
msgstr ""
"Cumasaigh antialiasing ama (TAA) i dteannta (nó in ionad) MSAA. Ós rud é gur "
"modh antialiasing spáis scáileáin é TAA, déanfaidh sé rud ar bith a "
"réiteach. Mar mhíbhuntáiste, déanann TAA go bhfuil an radharc níos doiléire "
"freisin, go háirithe ag rúin faoi bhun 1440p. Soláthraíonn TAA caighdeán "
"níos fearr i gcomparáid le FXAA agus féadann sé dul i ngleic go héifeachtach "
"ar aliasing Mar sin féin, tá costas feidhmíochta níos mó ag TAA i gcomparáid "
"le FXAA, agus is féidir le TAA déantáin ghosting a thabhairt isteach le "
"gluaiseacht tapa."

msgid ""
"Render the scene at a higher resolution by increasing the **Scaling 3D > "
"Scale** project setting above ``1.0``. This technique is called supersample "
"antialiasing (SSAA) and is very slow. Its use is generally only recommended "
"for offline rendering."
msgstr ""
"Cuir an radharc ar fáil ar thaifeach níos airde tríd an socrú tionscadail "
"**Scálú 3D > Scála** a mhéadú os cionn ``1.0``. Tugtar antialiasing "
"supersample (SSAA) ar an teicníc seo agus tá sé an-mhall. Go ginearálta ní "
"mholtar é a úsáid ach amháin le haghaidh rindreála as líne."
